  "prompt": "How do I save an answer on Quora?",
  "response": "To save an answer on Quora, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Find the Answer**: Navigate to the answer you want to save on Quora using a web browser or the Quora mobile app.\n\n2. **Save the Answer**:\n   - **On the Website**: Below the answer, you'll see several icons. Click on the bookmark icon (it looks like a ribbon). The icon will turn green, indicating that the answer has been saved.\n   - **On the Mobile App**: Tap on the more options icon (three dots) below the answer, and then tap \"Save\". You'll see a confirmation that the answer has been saved.\n\n3. **Access Saved Answers**: \n   - **On the Website**: Click on your profile picture in the top right corner, then select \"Profile\" and navigate to the \"Saved\" tab.\n   - **On the Mobile App**: Tap on your profile picture, then tap on \"Profile\", and go to the \"Saved\" section.\n\nYou can organize your saved answers into different collections if you wish, making it easier to find them later. Simply go to your saved items, and you can create and name new collections or add the answer to an existing collection.",
